'''Southlinch''' was a brand of pipeweed from [[Bree]]. [[Barliman Butterbur]] commented that its quality was no match for that from the [[Southfarthing]].<ref>{{RK|Homeward}}, p. 991</ref> It was named after the hill fields on the southern side of [[Bree-hill]].<ref>{{HM|UI}}, entry ''Southlinch'', p. 653</ref>
